Interface SpawningAlgorithm

public interface SpawningAlgorithm
Defines a spawning algorithm for creating food pieces at set intervals.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type
    Method
    Description
    Point[]
    update(Point[] empty, int timeAlive)
    This method will be called every game tick.

  • Method Details

    • update

      Point[] update(Point[] empty, int timeAlive)
      This method will be called every game tick. The game will use the return value to determine where to spawn new food.
      Parameters:
      empty - all unoccupied points at which the game could spawn food
      timeAlive - number of updates since the game began
      Returns:
      an array of points at which the game will attempt to spawn food
